Reference-contexts: While some companies view HFC as a means to simply expand the offering of cable channels available to consumers, other HFC visionaries are designing switched digital video (SDV) networks, which will offer a superior level of interactivity and flexibility <ref> [4] </ref>. 2.1 HFC Today Since higher frequencies attenuate faster than lower frequencies, adding more channels to the traditional all-coaxial cable network means adding more coax amplifiers. Noise and distortion is added logarithmically, and picture quality deteriorates along the amplifier cascade. In addition, each amplifier introduces another point of common failure.
